<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Masoud Makrehchi</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Academic & Industry Leader | Expert in Generative AI, NLP, Machine Learning & Responsible Innovation | Bridging Research and Executive Strategy | Author"
  />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f7f7f9;
      --fg: #222;
      --accent: #1a73e8;
      --muted: #666;
      --card-bg: #ffffff;
      --border: #dddddd;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
        sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--fg);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    header {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 960px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .top-bar {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .name-block h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .name-block p {
      margin: 0.2rem 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    nav {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    nav a {
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-right: 1.2rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    nav a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    main {
      padding-top: 1rem;
    }

    section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    }

    section h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
    }

    ul {
      margin-top: 0.2rem;
      padding-left: 1.1rem;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    }

    .tagline {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
    }

    .links a {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-right: 1rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .links a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    footer {
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 1rem 0 2rem 0;
      background: #ffffff;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    footer p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: center;
    }

    @media (min-width: 720px) {
      .top-bar {
        flex-direction: row;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="top-bar">
        <div class="name-block">
          <h1>Masoud Makrehchi</h1>
          <p>Ph.D, P.Eng, SMIEEE</p>
          <p class="tagline">
            Academic &amp; Industry Leader | Expert in Generative AI, NLP,
            Machine Learning &amp; Responsible Innovation | Bridging Research
            and Executive Strategy | Author
          </p>
        </div>
        <nav>
          <a href="#about">About</a>
          <a href="#research">Research Interests</a>
          <a href="#roles">Academic &amp; Professional Roles</a>
          <a href="#philosophy">Philosophy &amp; Vision</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <section id="about">
        <h2>About Myself</h2>
        <p>
          I am Masoud Makrehchi, a researcher, educator, and team leader with
          deep expertise in Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and
          Natural Language Processing. Since starting my PhD at the University
          of Waterloo (2002) and finishing in 2007, I have built a career that
          spans both academia and industry, striving to link rigorous theory
          with meaningful real-world impact.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="research">
        <h2>Research Interests &amp; Focus</h2>
        <p>My current scholarship and investigations center on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Large Language Models (LLMs) &amp; Generative AI: exploring their
            capacities, behaviors, and limits.
          </li>
          <li>
            Responsible AI &amp; Ethics: balancing innovation with safeguarding
            fairness, interpretability, and accountability.
          </li>
          <li>
            Natural Language Processing (NLP): work in text representation,
            entity extraction, and taxonomy induction.
          </li>
          <li>
            AI/ML Applications in Legal &amp; Financial Domains: applying models
            to contracts, legal text analytics, and finance.
          </li>
          <li>
            Moral AI Agents &amp; Algorithm Design: embedding normative behavior
            or constraints in autonomous systems.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="roles">
        <h2>Academic &amp; Professional Roles</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            As a professor and mentor, I have guided graduate and undergraduate
            students toward impactful research, emphasizing both theoretical
            rigor and application relevance.
          </li>
          <li>
            I serve as an advisor and research collaborator in both academic and
            industry settings, helping bridge the gaps between scientific
            insight and product deployment.
          </li>
          <li>
            My publication record includes peer-reviewed papers, conference
            presentations, and invited works. I also contribute to surveys,
            toolkits, and curated reading lists, helping advance community
            resources in ML and NLP.
          </li>
          <li>
            I maintain a public platform sharing reading lists, tools, and
            reflections (for example, LLM reading list, ML surveys) to
            encourage open discourse and resource sharing.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="philosophy">
        <h2>Philosophy &amp; Vision</h2>
        <p>
          From my vantage point, working with generative models is not just a
          technical challenge but a moral and societal one. I approach every
          line of code, every model experiment, and every collaboration through
          a lens of responsibility, hopeful about the future of AI but vigilant
          about its limits and risks.
        </p>
        <p>
          I view my role as a connector: between students and ideas, between
          academia and industry, and between innovation and ethics. My aim is to
          contribute to AI systems and knowledge that are not only advanced but
          also socially beneficial, transparent, and aligned.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="links">
        <h2>Links</h2>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/masoud-makrehchi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            My LinkedIn page
          </a>
          <a href="https://medium.com/@makrehchi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            My Medium page
          </a>
          <!-- Add your GitHub profile and other links here if you like -->
          <!-- <a href="https://github.com/your-github-username" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">My GitHub</a> -->
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <p>&copy; <span id="year"></span> Masoud Makrehchi. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    // Set current year in footer
    document.getElementById("year").textContent =
      new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
</body>
</html>

</body>
</html>

